#Vengeful Rebirth (#1085): return a card from my graveyard to hand; a nonland
#return also deals its mana value to any target; the spell exiles itself.
#Return hill giant (mv 3), point 3 at the opponent: life 17, giant in hand,
#rebirth in exile.
#PARK UPDATE 2026-06-11 evening: DATA FIX LANDED - the 22 'choice name(X)
#:target(...)' colon sites in this card's buckets parsed as phantom
#zero-cost ACTIVATED abilities (the leading colon hits the cost-split);
#colons removed, and a choose-one menu NOW SPAWNS (choice 1 = the mv3
#bucket accepts, hill giant click lands). REMAINING: the accepted GTA never
#fires through the stack after the target click (no StackAbility), and the
#self-exile line (moveto(myexile) all(this)) never fires either - the
#rebirth ends in the graveyard. Suspect the spell-source lifecycle (the
#instant leaves the stack at resolution; the may/GTA source is a non-
#battlefield card) - instrument the click routing + ALord all(this) on a
#resolving instant next. Driving so far: cast, pads, choice 1, giant click.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{4}{R}{G}
hand:vengeful rebirth
graveyard:hill giant,darksteel citadel
[PLAYER2]
[DO]
vengeful rebirth
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 1
goto firstmain
hill giant
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 0
p2
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
hand:hill giant
exile:vengeful rebirth
graveyard:darksteel citadel
[PLAYER2]
life:17
[END]
